<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="negotiate-v">negotiate <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /nɪ'ɡəʊʃieɪt/    美 /nɪ'ɡoʊʃieɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>谈判；协商</strong></h4>
<p>to try to reach an agreement by formal discussion, especially in business or politics：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The government refused to <strong>negotiate with</strong> terrorists.
政府拒绝与恐怖分子谈判。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We have been <strong>negotiating for</strong> more pay.
我们一直在为增加工资进行协商。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-vt">2.★ <strong>vt 商定；达成 (协议)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>negotiate a deal / contract
达成交易 / 确立合同</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>negotiable /nɪ'ɡəʊʃiəbl/ adj   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The minister said, “We are ready for discussions with any legal parties, but we’ll never negotiate <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ criminals.”  （2011 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. with  </p></div>